  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 36 airports right now. Engine anti-ice operations are flagged at Suceava Stefan cel Mare (SCV/LRSV). Across base airports: 19 critical, 6 high, 8 medium, 6 normal. Key bases needing attention include Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR), Cluj Avram Iancu (CLJ/LRCL) and Chişinău (RMO/LUKK); plus 22 other bases. 8 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, mist and low cloud base  — most notably around Suceava Stefan cel Mare (SCV/LRSV), Chişinău (RMO/LUKK) and Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP). Network hotspots: Suceava Stefan cel Mare (SCV/LRSV), Sofia (SOF/LBSF), Bucharest Băneasa Aurel Vlaicu (BBU/LRBS), Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP), Chişinău (RMO/LUKK) and 31 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, snow / blowing snow and mist. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Sofia (SOF/LBSF), Bucharest Băneasa Aurel Vlaicu (BBU/LRBS), Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP) and 9 others.",
